ABUJA – Mr. Kashifu Inuwa Ab­dullahi, Director Gen­eral/Chief Executive Officer of National Information Technolo­gy Development Agen­cy(NITDA) has said Data Protection Compliance Organizations (DPCOs) in Nigeria have created about 7,680 jobs for Ni­gerians in 2021. Abdullahi who stated this on Monday in Abuja at the National Privacy Week 2022 Media Con­ference, explained that the Agency has licensed about 103 DPCOs, with the mandate to “car­ry out Data Protection Regulations Compliance and Breach Services for Data Controllers and Data Administrators; Training and Aware­ness Services and Priva­cy Breach Remediation Planning and Support, among others.” He revealed that the Agency in the last one year has put necessary measures in place for data privacy protection of Ni­gerians.